<HEAD>Reagan Names Replacement For Pendleton At Civil Rights Commission</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The head of the Leadership Conference on Civil
Rights is attacking President Reagan's decision to elevate William
Barclay Allen to the chairmanship of the U.S. Commission on Civil
Rights.
   ``Regrettably the president has named another right-wing
ideologue as chairman of the civil rights commission,'' Ralph Neas
