<1ST_LINE>u i PM-Israel 1stLd-Writethru a0525 08-09 0468</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Israel, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0525,0478</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Israelis Kill 14-Year-Old Palestinian</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Updates throughout with killing of Palestinian teen-ager,
attack in Lebanon. Editing for transition. No pickup.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By RONI RABIN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Israeli troops shot and killed a 14-year-old
Palestinian and wounded eight other Arabs today, hospital officials
said. Israeli warplanes destroyed a radio station in Lebanon that
reportedly broadcast orders to the occupied territories.
   The latest fatality brought the Palestinian death toll to 238 in
the uprising in the occupied territories, now in its ninth month.
Four Israelis have been killed.
   In Israel's 12th air raid on southern Lebanon this year, a
military spokesman said the air force destroyed a PLO-run radio
station and an ammunition storehouse in southern Lebanon. Police in
Lebanon said three guerrillas were killed and 12 wounded in the
attack near Sidon.
   Commercial life was at a standstill today in Arab east Jerusalem
and at least eight cities in the occupied lands in observance of a
general strike called by pro-Palestine Liberation Organization
underground leaders.
   Arab merchants shuttered their shops and many of the 110,000 who
work in Israel stayed home from their jobs, Arab news reports and
witnesses said. Buses and taxis also stayed off roads, most of
which were deserted or blocked by protesters burning tires,
witnesses said.
   In the West Bank, Hussein Swei, 14, was fatally shot in the head
during a clash today between soldiers and dozens of Arab youths who
hurled stones, according to a spokesman at a U.N. clinic in
Qalqilya.
   The army said it was investigating the death, adding that a
curfew was imposed on the town after disturbances. The West Bank
town of Tulkarem also was placed under curfew.
   Hospital officials reported eight people wounded today. But a
military spokesman said the army could immediately confirm only two
Arabs shot in the Gaza Strip city of Khan Yunis.
   In the Gaza Strip today, an 18-year-old man from the Mugazi
refugee camp was rushed to Ahli Arab Hospital in Gaza City after
soldiers shot him in the chest during a clash, hospital officials
said.
   Two other Arab protesters were shot in the legs during the same
incident, the officials added, speaking on condition of anonymity.
   Soldiers also wounded three other Gazans in the town of Khan
Yunis during a protest that began when Arab activists tried to
prevent other Palestinians from heading to jobs in Israel, hospital
officials said. The army confirmed two of the wounded.
   In the West Bank city of Hebron, soldiers fired at protesters
who hurled stones at the city hall building and blocked a road with
burning tires, wounding two, according to officials at a local
clinic.
   The army confirmed that soldiers fired live ammunition to quell
a protest in Hebron, but said it had no reports of injuries.
</TEXT>
