<2ND_LINE>PM-Space Committee,150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Corporate Leaders Appointed To Space Advisory Committee</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Commerce Secretary C. William Verity has
announced the establishment of the Commercial Space Advisory
Committee to recommend ways to increase U.S. business presence in
space ventures and activities.
   ``The U.S. needs to forge a stronger link between our vast
science and technology resources and U.S. corporations and
entrepreneurs ... to ensure an economic environment where U.S.
space commerce can thrive,'' Verity said in a statement Monday.
   The 15-member panel, composed of representatives from industry,
government and higher education, is scheduled to make
recommendations to the administration by the end of October, when
its authorization expires.
   All but two of the committee members represent corporations not
traditionally associated with space ventures. Ed Hood, vice
president of General Electric Co., will serve as chairman of the
group which also includes governors Bob Martinez of Florida and
John D. Waihee of Hawaii.
