<1ST_LINE>r w PM-Reagan-Bush     08-09 0203</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Reagan-Bush,190</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>First, Second Families Will Do Lunch Thursday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan, Vice President George Bush
and their wives will have lunch together Thursday and the two men
will address Cabinet members and political appointees on Friday
about the presidential campaign, the White House said today.
   Presidential spokesman Marlin Fitzwater said it was still
uncertain whether Reagan and Bush will meet during the Republican
National Convention in New Orleans next week.
   Reagan is to fly to New Orleans on Sunday and leave on Tuesday
for his ranch near Santa Barbara, Calif. The vice president, who is
scheduled to receive the GOP presidential nomination on Wednesday,
is due to arrive in New Orleans the day Reagan leaves.
   The president and vice president frequently have lunch together
in the Oval Office, most recently on July 28. Fitzwater said
Thursday's lunch would also give Barbara Bush and first lady Nancy
Reagan an opportunity to compare notes on the campaign.
   Fitzwater said he did not know whether Friday's meeting would be
public. It is believed to be the first time Reagan and Bush have
appeared together in a political setting since the president
endorsed the vice president after he nailed down the presidential
nomination.
