<2ND_LINE>PM-Kahn,0124</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Richard Kahn Elected President of Motion Picture Academy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Marketing executive Richard Kahn
has been elected as the 26th president of the Academy of Motion
Picture Arts and Sciences, sponsors of the Academy Awards.
   Kahn, the first member of the public relations branch of the
academy to be elected president, succeeds director Robert Wise.
Elected last week as vice presidents of the academy were writer
Norman Corwin, public relations executive Charles M. Powell and New
World Pictures head Robert Rehme.
   Cinematographer Joseph Westheimer was reelected as treasurer,
and editor Donn Cambern was named secretary. The academy also
elected 13 governors to its 36-member board, including director
Norman Jewison and producer Saul Zaentz.
</TEXT>
