<BYLINE>Company To Sell Glass Fabrics Division</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>GREENVILLE, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   JPS Textile Group Inc. on Tuesday
announced it intends to sell its JPS Glass Fabrics Division.
   The division manufactures woven and non-woven fiberglass fabrics
for the electronics, building products, insulation, filtration and
aerospace defense industries.
   A spokesman said the Glass Fabrics Division had sales of
approximately $72 million for the 12 months ending April 30.
   The division is headquartered in Slater and has manufacturing
facilities in both Slater and Walterboro.
   JPS Textile Group is a holding company formed by Odyssey
Partners and certain other investors pursuant to the acquisition of
certain assets from J.P. Stevens & Co. Inc. in May, the company
said in a statement.
