<HEAD>Passenger Traffic Up in First Half of Year</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New throughout to CORRERCT from commercial airlines to IATA
member airlines on international flights regarding passenger
figures. No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>GENEVA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Airlines belonging to the International Air
Transport Association carried nearly 88 million passengers on
international flights in the first half of 1988, up 6 percent over
the same period last year, the industry group said Tuesday.
   Guenter Eser, the director general of the IATA, which represents
172 airlines, said the growth rate is in line with long-term
industry forecasts after stagnation in 1986 and a sharp rebound
last year.
